thread.title: Gas prices fall 2 cents in New Hampshire
thread.title_full: Gas prices fall 2 cents in New Hampshire - WCAX.COM Local Vermont News, Weather and Sports-

author: wcax.com
title: Gas prices fall 2 cents in New Hampshire
text:
CONCORD, N.H. (AP) - Gas prices in New Hampshire fell 2 cents per gallon in the past week, to an average of $2.16.
Gasbuddy.com, which surveyed 875 gas stations in the state, says that's 13 cents lower than the national average, which went up half a cent to $2.29 a gallon.
Gas prices in New Hampshire are $1.16 lower than they were a year ago, and 14.6 cents per gallon lower than a month ago.
The national average is 11.4 cents per gallon lower than it was a month ago and 99.5 cents per gallon lower than a year ago.
